What is Express Response Object?

The Response object (res) represents the HTTP response that an Express app sends back to the client.

app.get('/', (req, res) => {
  res.send('Hello World');
});

1. res.app Property
Purpose

Returns the Express application instance.

Example
app.get('/', (req, res) => {
  console.log(res.app === app); // true
  res.send('App accessed');
});

Use Case

Access app-level settings from middleware

2. res.headersSent Property
Purpose

Checks if response headers have already been sent.

Example
if (res.headersSent) {
  console.log('Headers already sent');
}

Use Case

Prevent sending response multiple times

3. res.locals Property
Purpose

Stores response-local variables accessible in views.

Example
app.use((req, res, next) => {
  res.locals.username = 'Saraswati';
  next();
});

Use Case

Pass data to templates

4. res.append() Function
Purpose

Adds HTTP response headers without overwriting existing ones.

Syntax
res.append(field, value);

Example
res.append('Warning', '199 Miscellaneous warning');

5. res.attachment() Function
Purpose

Sets Content-Disposition header for file download.

Example
res.attachment('report.pdf');
res.send('File ready');

Output

Forces browser to download file

6. res.cookie() Function
Purpose

Sets a cookie on the client.

Syntax
res.cookie(name, value, options);

Example
res.cookie('user', 'admin', { maxAge: 60000 });
res.send('Cookie set');

7. res.clearCookie() Function
Purpose

Deletes a cookie.

Example
res.clearCookie('user');
res.send('Cookie cleared');

8. res.download() Function
Purpose

Sends a file and forces download.

Example
res.download('files/report.pdf');

9. res.end() Function
Purpose

Ends the response without sending data.

Example
res.end();

Use Case

Low-level response handling

10. res.send() Function
Purpose

Sends a response body (string, object, array).

res.send('Hello');
res.send({ success: true });

11. res.json() Function
Purpose

Sends a JSON response.

res.json({ name: 'Ram' });

12. res.status() Function
Purpose

Sets HTTP response status code.

res.status(201).send('Created');

13. res.sendStatus() Function
Purpose

Sets status code and sends status message.

res.sendStatus(404);

14. res.set() Function
Purpose

Sets response headers.

res.set('Content-Type', 'text/plain');

15. res.get() Function
Purpose

Returns response header value.

res.get('Content-Type');

16. res.redirect() Function
Purpose

Redirects the client.

res.redirect('/login');

17. res.type() Function
Purpose

Sets the response Content-Type.

res.type('json');

18. res.links() Function
Purpose

Sets Link HTTP header fields.

res.links({
  next: '/page/2',
  last: '/page/5'
});

19. res.location() Function
Purpose

Sets Location HTTP response header.

res.location('/new-path');

20. res.vary() Function
Purpose

Adds field to the Vary HTTP header.

res.vary('User-Agent');

Summary Table (Viva Friendly)
Function / Property	Purpose
res.app	Access app instance
res.headersSent	Check headers status
res.locals	Store response locals
res.append()	Add headers
res.attachment()	File attachment
res.cookie()	Set cookie
res.clearCookie()	Remove cookie
res.download()	Download file
res.end()	End response
res.send()	Send response
res.json()	Send JSON
res.status()	Set status
res.redirect()	Redirect
